From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Subject: [PATCH] dma: omap: high L3 read-priority for the cyclic (audio) sDMA channel

EXPERIMENT / beyond-stock. The residual playback crackle on the Nexus Q is
McBSP2 sDMA FIFO starvation: the audio DMA refill reads from DDR lose L3/EMIF
arbitration to the other bus masters this image runs (WiFi SDIO, the USB-eth
LAN9500A, the LXQt/Wayland desktop, PulseAudio), which the minimal stock
appliance never had -- so the FIFO underflows and playback clicks. A2DP (a
native-48 kHz input, no resampling) drops identically to librespot, isolating
the fault to the common output path PA -> TAS5713 -> sDMA -> McBSP2.

mainline defines CCR_READ_PRIORITY (BIT 6, the channel's L3 read-port priority)
but never sets it, and inits GCR with HI_THREAD_RESERVED=0. Stock also left the
per-channel bit clear (its priority plumbing is inert for audio) but did set
GCR HI_THREAD_RESERVED=1 (GCR=0x11010). This goes one deliberate step beyond
stock: mark ONLY the cyclic channel (which on this appliance is the audio path)
high read-priority, so the elevation stays relative -- bulk/memcpy transfers
keep normal priority -- and set GCR HI_THREAD_RESERVED=1 so a high-priority
sDMA thread FIFO slot is actually reserved for it. To be validated on-device
(does the crackle drop?); cleanly revertible if it does not help.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
 drivers/dma/ti/omap-dma.c | 21 +++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/dma/ti/omap-dma.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/ti/omap-dma.c
@@ -1197,6 +1197,20 @@
 	else
 		d->ccr |= CCR_DST_AMODE_CONSTANT | CCR_SRC_AMODE_POSTINC;

+	/*
+	 * Nexus Q (steelhead): raise this channel's L3 READ priority. Cyclic
+	 * DMA on this appliance is the audio path (McBSP2 -> TAS5713 / McASP
+	 * S/PDIF); for playback (MEM_TO_DEV) the source is DDR, so the periodic
+	 * refill reads compete on L3/EMIF with WiFi SDIO, the USB-eth LAN9500A
+	 * and the LXQt desktop -- when they win, the McBSP2 sDMA FIFO underflows
+	 * and playback crackles. Marking only the cyclic (audio) channel high
+	 * read-priority keeps the elevation relative (bulk/memcpy stay normal).
+	 * Beyond stock (stock ran a minimal appliance with far less bus
+	 * contention and left this bit clear); paired with GCR HI_THREAD_RESERVED=1
+	 * so a high-priority sDMA thread FIFO slot is actually reserved.
+	 */
+	d->ccr |= CCR_READ_PRIORITY;
+
 	d->cicr = CICR_DROP_IE;
 	if (flags & DMA_PREP_INTERRUPT)
 		d->cicr |= CICR_FRAME_IE;
@@ -1827,7 +1841,10 @@
 		}
 	}

-	omap_dma_init_gcr(od, DMA_DEFAULT_ARB_RATE, DMA_DEFAULT_FIFO_DEPTH, 0);
+	/* tparams=1: reserve one high-priority sDMA thread (GCR HI_THREAD_RESERVED,
+	 * stock steelhead value 0x11010) so the audio channel's CCR_READ_PRIORITY
+	 * above has a reserved FIFO slot to win L3 arbitration. */
+	omap_dma_init_gcr(od, DMA_DEFAULT_ARB_RATE, DMA_DEFAULT_FIFO_DEPTH, 1);

 	if (od->cfg->needs_busy_check) {
 		od->nb.notifier_call = omap_dma_busy_notifier;
